            . I am an apprentice to Mr. Prichard, watch-spring-maker, of Wynatt-street. On the 14th of November, about five o'clock in the afternoon, I was by Clerkenwell-church, and heard a cry of Stop him, and saw the prisoner running with a bag in his hand, I followed and dodged him, he then threw it behind him, and behind me, I pursued and caught him, went back immediately, and took the bag up and gave it to 
               <persName id="t18221204-114-person1058">
                  Ann 
                  Bowles
               <interp inst="t18221204-114-person1058" type="surname" value="Bowles"></interp>
